title: Larry Colwell Dance Photographs, 1944-1966
subjects: writings;articles;performing arts;arts and culture;clippings (information artifacts);photographic prints;dance;black-and-white-negatives;music;contact sheets;promotional materials
description: Photographs of dance and dancing are vital visual documentation of dance practices and performance in the United States. This digital collection represents the entire contents of the Music Division’s collection of Larry Colwell Dance Photographs. In studio portraits, Colwell captured many ballet stars of the Ballet Russe de Monte Carlo and the New York City Ballet. He also developed a technique for photographing live dance whose aesthetic used blurring to connote the excitement of seeing the moving dancer.
